   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11593.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hasted delays ARE fractional</span><hr size=1> Level 60 clr, 14/25 1hb, 175 hb skill, no haste, atk = 805. Target SB in SH.<br>
<br>
Local time from first swing till last swing: <br>
- 33:05 (or 330.7 ticks)<br>
<br>
Server time from first swing till last swing based on HP regen: <br>
- 327 ticks<br>
<br>
Swings: 788<br>
Hits: 468 (59%)<br>
Misses: 320 (41%)<br>
<br>
Avg hit: 8.2 (laugh)<br>
Dps: 1.93<br>
<br>
Now, 327 ticks * 6 sec / 2.5 sec/swing = 784.8 swings rather than 787 as &quot;expected&quot; (not 788 as that includes a swing in both ends of the sample). <br>
<br>
So, for the numbers to fit I must have somehow missed a server tick despite my method (328*6/2.5 = 787.2).<br>
<br>
A longer sample is probably a good idea though - 10 times longer comes to mind - but I doubt I have the patience for that.<br>
<br>
