 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unimbletoekneeslapper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NimbletoeKneeslapper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boisdarc.tamu-commerce.edu/~kev/NimDance3.gif WIDTH=22 HEIGHT=22" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/22/02 4:19:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11593.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hasted delays ARE fractional</span><hr size=1> it would stand to reason the dex bonuses (like str bonuses) are not given to the offhand weapon regarding proc.  This would explain the difference between main and offhand proc rates, and also give you the number for dex bonus. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uparticleboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>particleboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/22/02 4:34:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11593.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hasted delays ARE fractional</span><hr size=1> &quot;it would stand to reason the dex bonuses (like str bonuses) are not given to the offhand weapon regarding proc. &quot;<br>
