You are using a 20 delay weapon... try a shardwurm stinger which should be easily obtained with a delay of 40 piercing (rusty spear is 38). Rusty bastard sword all have delay of 42 for 1HS. Rusty morning star for 1HB is delay 44. Tarnished and bronze also have the same delays as the rusy weapons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umonkeybass.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MonkeyBass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/27/02 8:49:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11593.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hasted delays ARE fractional</span><hr size=1> Wouldn't way of thinking about be better to make the haste an average number of swings gained over the same period of time? Put 1hs in one hand, 1hb in other, go to town, parse out 1hb. Rinse repeat several time get an average number swings gained with the same haste/stats/buffs verses same set-up no haste. Without knowing how most of these things are REALLY calculated is most of this exercise somewhat futile?<br>
